$Lexi Fam

We're excited to announce the release of our groundbreaking, never-seen-before SMS-to-Crypto tech. With this, you can buy/sell, check token prices, manage your portfolio, and audit contracts—all via SMS.

How to use:

1. First, add +1 (579) 793-4803 to your phone contacts.
2. Open your messaging app and type /register to link a wallet. If you're sending the SMS from the same number you’ve used with our WhatsApp bot, you can skip this step.
3. Type out the contract and amount you want to buy/sell, and send the SMS.
4. You can also use all the other commands available on WhatsApp, like /token, /wallet, and /audit.

Once the message is successfully sent, you'll receive a reply with the response.

Prerequisites:

- You must have a working phone number with a cellular network capable of sending SMS internationally.
- Currently, our number is based in Canada, but we'll be rolling out local numbers for countries with the highest demand in the coming days.

cleaned_data.original_text:
Same cycle, same year, different skin.

#Bitcoin Blue Year has had the same structure each and every time.

Two significant highs, two sideways periods.

This cycle, we traded a shorter more powerful move from the January - March high for a longer correction afterward.

No cycle has ever been able to achieve ATHs in Blue Year like our current one has, which is why the correction is taking so long.

All highs you see here have taken about a month to find their bottom, while we are going on 5 months.

Now the good news.

Every second early top (light blue circle) has bottomed around August, for which our latest August drop looks like a likely culprit.

The month that that price makes new highs after that has been pushed forward each year.

New highs in September inbound? 

It's great to see that despite regular differences, the Halving Cycles Theory and a top in late 2025 look like it may have never derailed.

I think the “diminishing returns” observed in #BTC since 2013 is almost solely a function of shitcoin marketing and “dumb money.”

To think zero value projects like doge, bch, solana, and ethereum still collectively have almost $1T in fully diluted market cap… 😅

This is perhaps the most insane over-valuation (not in absolute, but certainly in relative terms) in the history of markets. 

The slow churn of these projects towards zero not only enriches their founders, but actually destroys invested capital. 

Should this capital have simply been accreted to Bitcoin-denominated savings on the margins, I suspect we would be at least 3X and perhaps as much as 10X higher in terms of USD-denominated BTC price.

cleaned_data.original_text:
Lots of pre fractal projects making the most of the hype but always remember what you’re getting yourself into

There is no comparison between collectibles on L1 BTC and scaling solutions like Fractal 

This image highlights a big difference 

Fractal is a scaling solution for Bitcoin 

Ordinals and Runes/BRC20 are on L1 Bitcoin 

There are dozens of teams working on scaling BTC, a lot of them still aren’t even in this image 

And this is amazing, especially for payments and other use cases for bitcoin

The goal is for people to be using bitcoin without even really realising they’re using crypto, which is where the scaling solutions come in

But collectibles are always more desirable and valuable on the main chain 

Just look at ETH vs ETH L2 NFTs

The biggest selling point for Ordinals is immutability on bitcoin

Speed of trading isn’t something needed for high-end artwork that you plan on holding for years

No doubt there is money to be made but just be wary of teams trying to extract value with the hype, or chasing something that’s already pumped, someone is always exit liquidity 

And this isn’t to say that teams won’t be building some great stuff (unisat and bitboy are awesome) but always be wary around the new and shiny hype 

It’s awesome to see new innovations and development on Bitcoin but remember the real deal will always be on L1 BTC 

Ordinals and Runes/BRC20 are where that is 

My personal view is Ordinals and Runes will be the most sustainable long-term but BRC20 still has a big market

If you like to play around and experiment with new things, then definitely learn more and get involved

But don’t get distracted from the real deal on L1

cleaned_data.original_text:
I'm in the process of writing an article on this right now that I will post later, but this graph is pretty extraordinary. 

It show the distribution of the following quantity:

log(P2/P2) / log(t2/t1) ,

where P2 is the price of Bitcoin today and P1 the price of Bitcoin yesterday, t2 is the time from the Genesis Block today and t1 the time of the Genesis Block yesterday. In other words log(P2/P1) is the log of the returns a very important quantity in understanding financial assets. 

It turns out that this quantity is a sort of "invariant" in average. 

It is a random distribution but the mean is the slope of the power law that we observe over the general trajectory (about 6). 

What is the interpretation of this? Basically every day we have a mini power law with a random slope but in average over all these years, this value is the overall power law. Almost like domains in a magnet that are randomly oriented but their general mean points in one direction. 

This is the key to understand why the price seems locally random but it follows overall a precise power law. This shows the power law is a much more profound property of the system that at first appears. 

It works "in average" at all scales. As a real scale invariant system should do. 
I didn't try smaller scales than days so far but I will soon. This works for years, months, weeks, days, probably will work all the way to hours and minutes. 

It is incredible that Bitcoin has both a deterministic component log(t2/t1) and a random one log(P2/P1) but when they combine they form an invariant (even if just in average) that has been true over 15 years and 8 orders of magnitude. 

The theoretical distribution in red here is a Laplacian with mu=5.895 and parameter b=54.

These two bitcoin animations received 2.3M impressions in the last 72 hours! 

A common saying is that school teaches us math, like cosines and the hypotenuse of a triangle, but we never use it at work. As an engineer I have to use math everyday to calculate satellite orbits and to predict signal strengths over great distances. 

I enjoy using my skills to visualize the mathematics of bitcoin so that everyone--the lawyers and the dishwashers--can understand the models that help me sleep easy when the prices goes down.

Seeing these videos succeed on X gives me a lot of joy. If they were helpful to you, consider hitting that repost button. It really helps us smaller accounts. 

I'll drop a few of my other charts in the comments for the people who don't know me.

The Case For Runestones As An Asset Class

Provenance
- Created by @LeonidasNFT one of the preeminent names in the #Ordinals & #Runes space.

- Mined The Largest Inscription In #Bitcoin History; Selling the "grandparent" for 8 BTC to fund the Runestone airdrop.

- The First Free & Fair Ordinals Drop: This wasn't waitlisted or individually minted - it was airdropped to early Ordinals

Unique Metrics
- Only 112,383 will ever be available as the child inscription was burned to Satoshi’s wallet. Runestones are 187x rarer than Bitcoin!

- 74.4k owners; high owner count of HODLers.

Growth & Revenue Potential

- Yield: Initial $DOG Runes airdrop of 100b tokens has generated over $1 billion in value to Runestone holders, with at least 2 more Runes air drops expected.

- Ecosystem: Bitcoin's ecosystem of Runes, Ordinals & BRC-20 tokens are expected to reach a market cap of $500b+ in the coming years.

- Market Cap: Runestones reached an all-time high market cap of nearly $750m on April 11th, 2024 with a price of $0.095114. 

RUNESTONE VALUE AS A % OF BTC MC ($1.2T)

- 0.1% MC: $10,679.12
- 0.2% MC: $21,358.24
- 0.3% MC: $32,037.35
- 0.4% MC: $42,716.47
- 0.5% MC: $53,395.59
- 0.6% MC: $64,074.71
- 0.7% MC: $74,753.82
- 0.8% MC: $85,432.94
- 0.9% MC: $96,112.06
- 1% MC: $106,791

- Runestone derivative $DOG, the #1 Rune, with a steady 40%+ market share of the total Runes MC (currently $700m+) is widely expected to retain its lead and expand as the Runes market cap does, towards $100b+

- Runes account for 35%+ all Bitcoin transactions, and this is only expected to grow for both Runes & Ordinals.

------

TL;DR: 
- Runestones were created by one of the most respected leaders in the burgeoning Bitcoin ecosystem.

- With only 112.4k Runestones created they are 187x rarer than Bitcoin with a potential price of over $100k/Runestone.

- Derivatives like $DOG have brought over $1b in value to holders of Runestones. More yield opportunities are expected in the future.

- Bitcoin ecosystem, primed for explosive growth, is expected to top $500b+ in the future.

It's amusing that people argue this is random.

The p-value is so low that it falls below computational limits, indicating an "effectively 0%" probability of randomness. #BTC

Math represents objective truth. If you want to debate it, you need to use mathematical arguments.

The "price range" of the #Bitcoin power law is not as wide as some people think or claim.

The range is essentially power law support, with the potential for temporary deviation to varying degrees above support, but in a way that seems to be diminishing over time.

Update on my Credit Cycle Indicators and Why I Flipped Bullish Last Week👇:

My overarching belief is that Bitcoin and crypto are risk assets, primarily driven by liquidity and appetite for risk. I've spent much of this year building indicators to find the best proxies for these factors, mainly focusing on the credit market.

These tools, combined with technicals for execution, have helped me navigate the past six months of chop in both directions relatively stress-free.

I use these tools to guide my market swings, and you'll see me reference them in my analysis.

With that in mind, let's dive into some key developments from last week that made me flip bullish:

1) Significant Upside Breakout in HY

The most notable event was a strong move in High Yield (HY), breaking out of the wedge we initially observed (https://t.co/wkk6fXfXgK).

Earlier in August, HY defended its 100-day MA from above during the volatility event. As of now, it has bounced back strongly and remains comfortably above both the 100- and 200-day MAs. From a technical perspective, I see no reason for this trend to reverse anytime soon.

I deem this significant because investors accepting lower yields for the same level of risk suggests increased market confidence, which is bullish risk.

Historically, sustained moves higher in HY have not coincided with sustained Bitcoin downtrends. 

If bearish bitcoin here, you must ask—is this time different? I lean towards no.

2) Credit Cycle Indicator Spiking Higher

In the same chart, you can see my credit cycle indicator spiking sharply, similar to what we saw in November 2023 and January 2024. Historically, Bitcoin tends to react positively to these bullish impulses. This adds another layer of confidence in a risk-on move. Confluence builds conviction, and these are solid green flags.

3) Credit Cycle Momentum Flipping Bullish (4h & 1d)

To dig deeper into trends, I use the delta between the short and long MAs of my credit cycle indicator. This helps me assess trend momentum and provides further confluence when taking positions.

I refer to the 4-hour as the "spark" and the 1-day as the "fuel." The spark can ignite a move but can’t sustain it without the fuel.

In Q1, the spark was ignited, and fuel provided support, leading to a sustained rally. However, we saw a spark without fuel in May, resulting in a short-lived move.

Now, for the first time since Q1, the spark seems to be supported by fuel. This setup fundamentally differs from the other rallies we've seen in the past six months, which is why I believe it's significant.

Execution

Thursday's sell-off rattled a few people. Equities, gold, and HY all rallied whilst bitcoin sold off; timeline full of bear porn.

However, given all the above data, I wanted to add to positions. The 57k level has been a key support level during this six-month range, so a test from above was critical.

I saw a sweep of stops at 57k, followed by a clear reclaim as an excellent spot to add to my position, and so I did.

Concluding

My bullish thesis will be invalidated if:
1) We see significant changes in the risk proxies and indicators I've outlined above.
2) We close below last week's wick at 56k.

Until then, I remain comfortably long. My base case is that we'll be much higher in a month.

Stay tuned

You probably have seem posts that show liquidity increasing and the poster declaring the bull market started. It is important to see relationships not just single quantities in isolation.

This why I made a liquidity price model of Bitcoin to see how it responds to change in liquidity. 

Where is the price relative to liquidity right now?
It is still above the price justified by the observed relationship between price and liquidity.

In the past all the bull markets started when the liquidity price model is above the real price, or the area is green. We are red right now. 

Notice though the gap is closing up that is a good sign. 
If everything repeats as in the past the bull market will not start until we get some green flashing.

cleaned_data.original_text:
The Ethical Long: Cycles and Capital Formation

Since August 11th/12th, I began writing thoughts to capture my mental model around identifying inefficient capital allocation in crypto assets, and the market forces that drive positioning on the margin – which I believe is under-recognized today due to what has been a programmatic supply overhang (re: alt emissions, chunky BTC/ETH sellers). 

The dislocation created by seemingly endless supply has resulted in four mass ~1B long liquidations this year, the most recent of which broke an 8-month BTC-trading range – which I interpret as a unique opportunity to challenge microstructure underpinning a) “flight to safety” positioning and b) decomposing what actually drives liquidity & markets.

My belief is that without new money: in a scenario where total available dollars available has shrunken vs. March & where previous-cycle ATHs have settled, order-book combativeness & psychology of the buyer vs. seller are the fulcrum underpinning how and why money moves

Herein, I seek to challenge the status-quo of what is considered the “safe” risk-barbell (BTC/SOL/Memes) by framing risk-reward in a structural way: starting at the majors and subsequently walking through the conditions that must be met to create a sustained trickle-down effect buoying alts, or specifically, “OTHERS.”

This is the result of my deep dive dissecting and reviewing L5Y price / volume / dilution history for 150+ names

🔥ATENCIÓN🔥

💥Hay una GRAN divergencia entre el #SP500 y #Bitcoin
💥A principios del 2024 ocurrió esto y el PRECIO de Bitcoin SUBIO

👉El precio de Bitcoin generalmente sigue los movimientos del mercado de valores de EE. UU
👉Cuando el S&P 500 sube, Bitcoin también sube
👉Por el contrario, cuando el S& ;P 500 cae, Bitcoin sigue su ejemplo.

🔹Esto se debe a que Bitcoin está influenciado por los mismos factores que el mercado de valores:
🔹La Liquidez, las tomas de ganancias y el optimismo de los inversores
🔹Por eso en agosto, cuando el sp500 cayó un 6% en 3 días por temores de recesión y por el carry trade del Yen, Bitcoin también cayó alrededor del 30% en poco tiempo
🔹Actualmente , el sp500 se recuperó y cotiza cerca de su máximo histórico.
🔹El tema de la divergencia, se debe a que si bien el SP500 se recuperó, Bitcoin todavía no
🔹En este momento, hay una brecha notable entre Bitcoin y el SP500

🔍Esta divergencia, podría ser similar a la de principios del 2024, cuando #Bitcoin finalmente subió para ponerse al día con el SP500 👀
